        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>The new air intake scoop, as shipped, has a coating that is not adequate for service. It must
                        be painted prior to use. If the new air intake scoop is not painted prior to use, the coating
                        color will fade, chalk and may become brittle.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove any hoses from the external air cleaner on the right (passenger) side.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four mounting bolts and the external air cleaner on the right (passenger)
                    side.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent eye injury, wear safety glasses at all times when disassembling or assembling
                        components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the old air scoop by center punching the mandrel in each mounting rivet
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116031">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0116031" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0116031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="248px" resolution="94"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Old Air Intake Scoop</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Shear the rivet head off with a suitable steel chisel
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116032">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0116032" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0116032.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Shear Rivet Head Off</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove any remaining rivet material from the holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Position the new air scoop with the air intake pointing toward the front of the vehicle
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0116033">(Figure 3)</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the new air scoop to the cab and align the air scoop mounting holes with the
                    existing holes. Use the scoop as a template to locate two additional hole locations (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116033">Figure 3</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116034">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0116033" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0116033.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="288px" resolution="94"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Align Hole Locations</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0116034" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0116034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Locating Additional Holes</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drill the two new hole locations with a 3/16 inch diameter drill.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new air scoop with the fasteners and washers provided in the kit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the external air cleaner and any hoses.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
